    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="6">
            <title>Rear Cover and Power Steering Idler Shaft</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install the power steering idler shaft into the rear cover. Make sure the
                    bore of the idler shaft is clean.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651350" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/d06117.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Retaining ring on idler shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a retaining ring on the end of the shaft without the threaded hole.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2611351" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/d06119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Idler shaft and retaining ring in installation tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put the threaded hole end of the idler shaft into the installation tool to set the
                    correct height. 34.6 &#177; 0.15 mm (1.362 &#177; 0.006 in)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651352" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd16/d1619.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Power steering idler shaft in transmission side of rear cover</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Power steering idler shaft (Section A-A)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2651353" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/d06120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Idler shaft in the rear cover assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not allow the retaining ring to contact the rear cover. Contact
                        may distort the retaining ring, adversely affecting its performance as a gear thrust surface.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the idler shaft in the rear cover at the correct location. Using the installation
                    tool, drive the idler shaft in the idler shaft bore in the transmission side of the rear cover,
                    until the installation tool bottoms out.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651354" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd16/d1618.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Power steering idler shaft installation height</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Power steering idler shaft</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear cover assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If installation tool is not available, use brass drift to install the idler shaft in the
                    rear cover to the correct height.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2561355" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/d06121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Idler shaft height measurement</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure idler shaft height, using a dial caliper. Idler shaft height should be 34.6
                    &#177; 0.15 mm (1.362 &#177; 0.006 in).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
